subject: resource/Campaign_to_Suppress_Bandits_in_Northwestern_China
object: The Campaign to Suppress Bandits in Northwestern China (西北剿匪) was a counter-guerrilla/counter-insurgency campaign the communists fought against the nationalist guerrilla force that mostly consisted of bandits and nationalist regular troops left behind after the nationalist government withdrew from mainland China.  The campaign was fought during the Chinese Civil War in the post-World War II era in the northwestern China, and resulted in communist victory.
